            <Title>Stipes</Title>
            <Text>Stipes (lat. stump)
#
#

Upon arrival Seekers got a Stump Amulet which acts as a life counter which decreases every day until The Decay. It’s starts at 3650 days (10 years) and when reached 0 - then Seeker time is over and it disappears from the world. Chance was used and whatever was achieved - was achieved. Game starts with Unnamed words “I am giving you another chance” and ends with the same phrase. Stamp acts as a reminder of a limited time that Seekers have to realise the given chance. 

Although there are many legends about Stump, but there is absolutely nothing can be done about increasing or resetting the counter. Initially Stump has almost no internal circles, but as Seeker grow in their skills internal circles starts to appear - it’s a sign of experience. Counter is rendered inside and updated every day.

Messages
- We are not given a short life but we make it short, and we are not ill-supplied but wasteful of it… Life is long if you know how to use it (c) Seneca
- Do you know what is the most popular regret that Seekers have just before the Decay? Don’t you think that your interest is the proof that you’re concerned that your life might be wasted?
- Biggest regret: Wish I’d had the courage to live a life true to myself, not the life others expected of me
- Timer going to run out anyway, how would you like to see your disappearance from this world? What kind of a man you wish to see when counter would show zero?
- The is nothing more inspirational than looking to the eyes of a man who does not fear  his own death
- Jump while you can - time will come and you wouldn’t able to do things that you can do now.
- We all afraid of death, but not a mare extinction, but the extinctions with insignificance. Man want to know that his life has somehow counted, 

